This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object tracking using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for appearance and motion feature integration. Additionally, the paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the field of computer vision. 

The paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it involves the use of machine learning algorithms for object tracking. 

The Learning (cs.LG) category is also a likely fit as the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for feature integration. 

The Robotics (cs.RO) category is another possible fit as object tracking is a crucial component of robotics, and the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for this purpose. 

Finally, the Multimedia (cs.MM) category is also a possible fit as the paper deals with object tracking in videos, which is a common multimedia application.
